Sorry excited for more than just Inbound, Dr Who returns this fall.
Have they had the new actress in any specials or anything yet? Haven't watched since Capaldi took over, tried for a few episodes but couldn't get into it

Capaldi was hard to get into I agree. Jodie Whittaker hasn’t had any released episodes or anything yet, just a teaser trailer where you mostly just see her silhouette and someone eating fish fingers and custard
oh and pizza

I guess technically she has had 1 part of an episode - about 2 minutes or less long- the regeneration scene, and all she says is “oh, brilliant” and smiles, then per the norm, TARDIS starts blowing up and shes fallling out
no "still not ginger?" Disappointed.
haha yea
I was hoping for a joke like “wonder what River’s going to think?”
I really hope they keep Michelle Gomez on. Honestly while I think the other people who played the Master did good - her Evil Mary Poppinsness is a whole new level of villain
lol i love Dr Who, but yea i couldn;t get into capaldi, especially when they added billie as his companion, just wasnt the same without souffle girl (I miss clara)
I was hoping for a spinoff with Jenna Coleman and Maise Williams but ¯\_(ツ)_/¯
I think Jodie had the Christmas Special no?
I know hands down, to date, David Tennant is THE doctor
She had her 2 minutes of glowing glitter explosions to “oh Brilliant”
that’s all we’ve had so far
haha Matt Smith, David Tennant, Tom Baker are all THE doctor in my eyes
Matt Smith was awesome, he is def second to me, I never really got into the older Dr Who Stuff, I tried to watch it but i think because i started with the newer series it spoiled me
Tennant - Eccleston - Smith out of the new ones. John Hurt, then Capaldi lol

yea the other part though is the older doctor who was meant for people who’s attention spans were way longer - also sci-fi was in it’s early days, they had to explain a lot of concepts way more than now
The crossover with Hurt, Tennant, and Smith was awesome, I was hoping that Eccleston was going to make an appearance at some point.
Yea me too. Eccleston has some issues with the show producer at that time apparently and wanted nothing more to do with Dr who, so he didn’t go on

I guess Moffat actually wrote him into the original script but had to write him out. he was originally going to be the war doctor or the weapon, can’t remember exactly.

Oh well John Hurt as like a cowboy version of the doctor was awesome - I want to see him show up more. I get not having him get his own full run, but it’d be awesome for him to keep randomly popping in.
but... he died back in 07 :disappointed:
oh… yea…he’d have to be all CGI. #NoDoctorDies
'17, not '07, don't make me feel that old lol
thought that year sounded odd, cuz i swear the 50th wasn’t that long ago
also, had no idea John Hurt was the wand salesman in the first Harry Potter lmao
woah mind blown. had no idea that he was either. they transformed his look pretty good
and he was a good actor
true that
